      "content": "i see. but it feels like a lot of those \"concerns\" are just excuses to keep cities exclusive or prevent progress. like, wouldn't the long-term pros of things like better transit and less sprawl just naturally outweigh those temporary growing pains? feels like the \"opposition\" is mostly just stuck in the past.",
